Encapsulation and Life of a Packet:
- Encapsulation is when each OSI/TCP layer adds its own header (and sometimes trailer) to the data before sending it to th elayer below
- Application Layer generates user data -> passed down through the stack
- Internet layer adds an IP header, creating an IP packet.
- Link layer (Ethernet/WiFi) adds a frame header and trailer -> creates a frame.

ðŸ“¦ Life of a Packet Example (TryHackMe search):
1. User types in a search.

2. App formats HTTP request.

3. TCP sets up 3-way handshake.

4. IP layer adds source/destination IPs.

5. Link layer encapsulates it in a frame.

6. Routers forward the packet toward the server.

7. Packet is decapsulated and interpreted by the server.
